==Chinese==
===[[wikipedia:Taiwanese Mandarin|Taiwanese Mandarin]]===
[[Pinyin]]: bǎngzhuāng
===[[Min Nan]]===
[[POJ]]: páng-chng

===Etymology===
*Originally from [[Min Nan]], this term is short for [[綁票]] ([[POJ]]: páng-phiò, to kidnap for ransom)+[[樁腳]] (莊腳, [[POJ]]: chng-kha village - Mandarin equivalent: [[鄉下]]).  The term "kidnap one's village for ransom" is a metaphor for when a politician earmarks money in a budget in order to benefit constituents in return for their political support, either in the form of campaign contributions or votes.

